- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network structures and diffusion processes in social and technological networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the design of efficient inference algorithms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper uses an $l_1$-regularized likelihood maximization framework for network structure inference. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the sample complexity and algorithmic aspects of network structure inference. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the information spreading and diffusion processes in networks.
